2014-06-30 13:52:56	smrtz|nix	Should I set my username and password to secure variables too, FlashCode, or does weechat do that automaticly?
2014-06-30 13:55:20	nils_2	why the username?
2014-06-30 13:55:42	nils_2	secure is to store sensible informations like password.
2014-06-30 13:55:43	smrtz|nix	nils_2: just because I can.
2014-06-30 13:56:10	nils_2	you can also store the word "and" in secure variable, but its useless
2014-06-30 13:56:44	smrtz|nix	nils_2: right, but I feel like having my login info secured isn't a bad idea, I get that the username isn't sensitive, but whatever.
2014-06-30 13:57:05	@FlashCode	you must set ${sec.data.something} in irc options
2014-06-30 13:57:12	@FlashCode	and define secured data with /secure set
2014-06-30 13:57:22	smrtz|nix	FlashCode: got it, thanks.
2014-06-30 13:57:23	@FlashCode	this is not automatic, if that's what you mean
2014-06-30 13:57:31	-->	bocaneri (~bocaneri@about/linux/staff/sauvin) has joined #weechat
2014-06-30 13:57:46	smrtz|nix	Yeah, I thought weechat might automaticly secure usernames and passwords.
2014-06-30 13:58:09	smrtz|nix	So if I used $(sec.data.freenodeusername)
2014-06-30 13:58:19	nils_2	nope
2014-06-30 13:58:31	smrtz|nix	Would I use /secure set freenodeusername "xxx"?
2014-06-30 13:58:36	nils_2	you'll have to manually add a value to secure
2014-06-30 13:58:53	@FlashCode	smrtz|nix: yes
2014-06-30 13:58:54	nils_2	yes.
2014-06-30 13:59:11	smrtz|nix	thanks!
2014-06-30 13:59:11	@FlashCode	nils_2: you copy/pasted my answer!
2014-06-30 13:59:32	nils_2	i am not that fast :-)
